<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Creating Your GitHub Webpage</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Here are steps that you need to create your own webpage in GitHub</h1>

    <ol>
        <li>You need to create an account with GitHub</li>
        <li>Make a repository in GitHub, e.g., username.github.io</li>
        <li>You need to download your code editor - Visual Studio Code is a great option</li>
        <li>Create an index.html file in your code editor</li>
        <li>Use HTML to build your website; start with a header and a photo for now.</li>
        <li>Save your preferred photo in the same folder as the HTML file you created earlier</li>
        <li>Here's how you can start with your header:</li>
    </ol>

    <pre>
        <code>
&lt;h1>Your Name Portfolio&lt;/h1>
        </code>
    </pre>

    <p>Then you can add an image:</p>

    <pre>
        <code>
&lt;h1>Your Name Portfolio&lt;/h1>
&lt;img src="./your-photo.jpg" alt="Your Photo" />
        </code>
    </pre>

    <ol start="8">
        <li>Once completed, do not forget to save the file</li>
        <li>Open your HTML file on your local machine and check if it works first</li>
        <li>Open your GitHub repository and select "Add a file"</li>
        <li>Open your file manager, then drag and drop both your photo and your HTML file into the repository</li>
        <li>Commit the files, then select the HTML file to check your code (just to make sure it is the correct file)</li>
        <li>View your webpage using your repository name in the browser</li>
        <li>Congratulations!</li>
    </ol>
</body>
</html>
